data.body:
In a standard full project, if you use a gamepad to enter a cheetah vehicle, the vehicle will continue to move forward until you exit the vehicle.

What is happening, is the moveMap binding for left stick Y is setting $mvForwardAction.  Then the input map is changed to vehicleMap which has no binding for left stick Y, so the value is not cleared when you let go.

There are two fixes for this, one that would stop the forward movement, and additional to make it function with a gamepad out of the box.

In scripts/client/client.cs

in the function clientCmdtoggleVehicleMap(%toggle), add the following between moveMap.pop() and vehicleMap.push()

```
  // clear movement    
  $mvForwardAction = 0;
  $mvBackwardAction = 0;
```

The above change fixes the core issue, but you still cannot operate the cheetah with the gamepad at this point.  The change below gets the gamepad working to control the cheetah.

In the scripts/client/default.bind.cs

At the end of the file after the other vehicleMap binds add the following:

```
  // bind the left thumbstick for steering
  vehicleMap.bind( gamepad, thumblx, "D", "-0.23 0.23", gamepadYaw );
  // bind the gas, break, and reverse buttons
  vehicleMap.bind( gamepad, btn_a, moveforward );
  vehicleMap.bind( gamepad, btn_b, brake );
  vehicleMap.bind( gamepad, btn_x, movebackward );
  // bind exiting the vehicle to a button
  vehicleMap.bindCmd(gamepad, btn_y,"getout();","");
```

That fixes the issue and feels like a good starting point for gamepad vehicle control.
